fields.customfield_10200:
*NOTE:* Acom API interchangeably uses Refresh or JWT token so ensure this works expected for the end user

* Call Acom API GET /asset/{id} 
** iOS = 0E6B243B-C464-428B-972E-0181DEEAEAA1
** Android = 27C86A59-2F7A-480D-B269-018231389274
* Compare the version returned from the GET asset Response 
** if current app version is less than the one in the response then inform the client to show an alert to the user informing them an app update is available
** ensure the back off timer resets if the new version from asset response is greater than the previous
* Exponential back off:
** 3 days (72 hours) after the message is displayed the first time
** 7 days (168 hours) after the message is displayed the second time
** 15 days (360 hours) after the message is displayed the third time
* *_From User Story AC:_* _If the version available on acom api is increased beyond the original version that was checked, the interval cycle starts over for the messaging with a minimum of 3 days since the last message was displayed before the app should show a message for this newer version that is available_
